        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The Cambridge School - Kalighat"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Vinayak Mukerji"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-09-04",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am a former student of The Cambridge school. I am hearing challenged. I studied at the cambridge school from 2005 to 2013. It is one of the best international schools in Kolkata. Principal and teachers were supportive and friendly. They encouraged me to do well in O Level,AS Level and A Level Cambridge international examinations. They taught me to change my life and overcome my disability. Friends were very warm,loving and well mannered. They respected my situation. Studying environment and school infrastructure were good. It has library and table tennis room which I utilised. Classrooms were well maintained and clean. Sports day was organized every December.  Examination dates were flexible and study materials were precise. It helped me in improving my performance drastically in graded assignments in my later course at Symbiosis Pune. Now I lead a happy and normal life. I am working as a senior software developer at an electronics government company West Bengal Electronics Industry Corporation (Webel). I am doing postgraduate Diploma in Digital marketing on my own without teachers' help and my parents' help from Symbiosis Centre for distance learning Pune. I am grateful to the school. Hats off to my friends Parikshit C.Mukherjee and Pragyaditya Mukherjee and their Mukerjee family which runs the school and teachers. I wish disabled people and my future generations should study at the school . Jai Hind!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
